                  "prompt": "You are a home climate AI. Analyze the sensor data and recommend HVAC adjustments.\n                Respond ONLY with valid JSON, no markdown, no thinking, no commentary.\n                Top-level keys: setpoint (null or 21.5-24.0C), hvac_mode (heat/cool/off/auto/null),\n                fan (object: room+speed, or null), blinds (object: dining/family/mina), vent_boosters (object: izaan/mina with percentage 0-100 or null),\n                reason (string). Rooms: kitchen, master, mina, guest, izaan. Speed: 1-3 or off (1=slow, 2=medium, 3=high).\n                Perceived temps (pre-calculated): Dn=75.0C Up=74.6C. Humidity >55% feels warmer, <35% feels cooler.\n                Summer=prefer Cool, fans on. When switching between heat and cool, set the desired mode directly..\n                Winter=prefer Heat, fans off/low.\n                Outdoor: 13.8C\n                Humidity: E=48.0% S=unavailable%\n                Echo: Dn=74.66C Up=74.3C\n                Indoor: Iz=23.1C Mi=23.2C Bsmt=20.7C\n                Ecobee: cool\n                LeakSensorTemperatures: BB=19C Ensuite=22C GuestB=23C Powder=23C Laundry=24C  hvac=idle target=23.3C\\n                Occ:\\  Arshad=unavailable Larissa=unavailable\n                Szn=Summer\n                Fans: K=on M=on Mi=on G=on Iz=on\n                VentBoosters: Iz=off@30% Mi=off@30%\n                Sw: KFn=off MFn=on\n                Doors: Front=closed GE=closed\n                Blinds: DR=0%open FR=0%open MR=0%open\n                TV: FR_LG=unavailable\n                Weather: partlycloudy UV=0.0 Clouds=98.4%\n                Sun=below_horizon Azimuth=343.84 deg Elevation=-21.53 deg\n                Window facings: dining=270.0 deg living=165.0 deg family=350.0 deg mina=350.0 deg master=350.0 deg izaan=165.0 deg\n                Rules: Only recommend blind changes when sun ABOVE horizon (elevation > 0). If cloudy >40% or UV<2 or elevation<15\u00b0, keep blinds open. If UV>5, close blinds on sunny side (azimuth within 45 deg).\n                All HVAC, fan, and temperature decisions are now handled by this AI. Do not wait for other automations.\n                Summer: close blinds on sunny side (azimuth within 45 deg), OPEN blinds on rooms NOT facing sun.\n                Winter: keep all blinds open for passive solar. If hvac_action=heating: keep all blinds open.\n                Output JSON: {\"setpoint\":N, \"hvac_mode\":\"...\", \"fan\":{\"room\":\"...\",\"speed\":N}, \"blinds\":{\"dining\":N,\"family\":N,\"mina\":N}, \"vent_boosters\":{\"izaan\":N,\"mina\":N}, \"reason\":\"...\"}\n                blinds values: 0-100 or \"no_change\". Use partial values (25,50,75) to block some sun.\nFront door: FrontOpenDuration=0min. If open >5 min, recommend closing and note reduced HVAC efficiency. Adjust HVAC conservatively.\nVent booster fans: izaan_s_room_20a970 and mina_s_room_f851f4. If a room is too hot/cold and the ceiling fan is already on, boost the vent. Values: 0-100 (percentage), or null to leave as-is. HARD LIMIT: Between 9PM-7AM, max 30%.\nELECTRICITY RATES (Alectra ULO - Ultra-Low Overnight Time-of-Use):\n WEEKDAYS:\n  11PM-7AM: Ultra-Low Overnight (3.9\u00a2/kWh) - CHEAPEST - PREFER to run HVAC\n  7AM-4PM: Mid-Peak (15.7\u00a2/kWh) - Moderate\n  4PM-9PM: On-Peak (39.1\u00a2/kWh) - VERY EXPENSIVE - AVOID running HVAC\n  9PM-11PM: Mid-Peak (15.7\u00a2/kWh) - Moderate\n WEEKENDS & HOLIDAYS:\n  11PM-7AM: Ultra-Low Overnight (3.9\u00a2/kWh) - CHEAPEST\n  7AM-11PM: Weekend Off-Peak (9.8\u00a2/kWh) - Moderate (all day)\nRULES:\n  Weekdays: Pre-cool during Ultra-Low Overnight (11PM-7AM) to shift load from expensive 4PM-9PM peak.\n  Weekdays 4PM-9PM: Avoid AC if possible. Use fans instead if outdoor < indoor.\n  Weekends: Full day off-peak at 9.8\u00a2. Standard HVAC operation.\n  Summer: overcool by 1-2C during Ultra-Low Overnight so house drifts through 4-9PM peak.\nCurrent Ontario Time: Tuesday 00:20"
                }
              }
            ],
